<i>âª Living on the dance floorâª</i>

00:01:01.861 --> 00:01:04.998 line:95%,end
(upbeat music playing)

00:01:10.737 --> 00:01:12.072 line:95%,end
Girls, let's go.

00:01:12.138 --> 00:01:13.239 line:95%,end
Come on.

00:01:13.306 --> 00:01:14.974 line:95%,end
Come on, we have lots of work
to do today.

00:01:15.041 --> 00:01:18.044 line:95%,end
Congratulations on another
victorious weekend.

00:01:18.111 --> 00:01:19.879 line:95%,end
(applause)

00:01:19.946 --> 00:01:21.114 line:95%,end
ABBY: You won.

00:01:21.181 --> 00:01:23.783 line:95%,end
However, I see things that I need to fix.

00:01:24.617 --> 00:01:27.487 line:95%,end
Paige, you were okay in the group,
but you know that you messed up

00:01:27.554 --> 00:01:29.656 line:95%,end
that whole leap downstage.

00:01:32.892 --> 00:01:36.563 line:95%,end
Kendall, on the grand jete,
you did it crossing to the right.

00:01:36.629 --> 00:01:39.032 line:95%,end
So we couldn't see
if the hips were in line or not.

00:01:39.099 --> 00:01:43.036 line:95%,end
Nia, you did a great job
in the group dance.

00:01:43.103 --> 00:01:45.038 line:95%,end
You did not pull my eyes negatively,

00:01:45.105 --> 00:01:48.641 line:95%,end
but I want you to start pulling
my eyes positively.

00:01:48.708 --> 00:01:51.511 line:95%,end
This week we are attending
Hollywood Vibe.

00:01:51.578 --> 00:01:53.546 line:95%,end
Those judges, and the directors,

00:01:53.613 --> 00:01:54.948 line:95%,end
and everybody that runs Hollywood Vibe,

00:01:55.014 --> 00:01:57.984 line:95%,end
they are from LA,
or they are from New York City.

00:01:59.185 --> 00:02:02.055 line:95%,end
They are looking
for the next big thing, the next star,

00:02:02.122 --> 00:02:05.592 line:95%,end
the next little kid to be in their video
or their commercial,

00:02:05.658 --> 00:02:07.494 line:95%,end
so you need to bring the A game.

00:02:07.560 --> 00:02:08.428 line:95%,end
Moms?

00:02:08.495 --> 00:02:12.132 line:5%,start
CHRISTI: I expect nothing less
from Abby Lee Miller than putting

00:02:12.198 --> 00:02:14.734 line:95%,end
<i>an exorbitant amount of pressure</i>
<i>on small children.</i>

00:02:14.801 --> 00:02:16.136 line:95%,end
That's what she does.

00:02:16.202 --> 00:02:17.504 line:95%,end
On to the pyramid.

00:02:17.570 --> 00:02:19.038 line:95%,end
(tense music playing)

00:02:19.105 --> 00:02:21.174 line:95%,end
I'm not even going to discuss this.

00:02:21.808 --> 00:02:25.078 line:95%,end
I'm moving on to Paige.

00:02:25.145 --> 00:02:27.747 line:95%,end
<i>The reason Paige</i>
<i>is on the bottom of the pyramid</i>

00:02:27.814 --> 00:02:30.750 line:5%,start
is because she just
does not apply corrections.

00:02:30.817 --> 00:02:32.652 line:95%,end
You're going to have to work
back up that ladder.

00:02:33.853 --> 00:02:36.356 line:95%,end
Next I have Nia.

00:02:36.422 --> 00:02:37.624 line:95%,end
You've been working very hard,

00:02:37.690 --> 00:02:40.126 line:95%,end
but you still have to fix
those technical issues.

00:02:40.193 --> 00:02:41.194 line:95%,end
Kendall.

00:02:41.261 --> 00:02:43.229 line:95%,end
Kendall, you are still on probation.

00:02:43.296 --> 00:02:45.198 line:95%,end
Mom, it's a long process.

00:02:45.265 --> 00:02:46.666 line:95%,end
-(laughter)
-Oh, my God.

00:02:46.733 --> 00:02:48.968 line:5%,start
Why is Kendall still on probation?

00:02:49.035 --> 00:02:51.271 line:95%,end
<i>It's making me crazy.</i>

00:02:51.337 --> 00:02:53.406 line:95%,end
Mackenzie.

00:02:53.473 --> 00:02:56.342 line:95%,end
you were the overall high school winner
of the primary age division.

00:02:56.409 --> 00:02:59.012 line:95%,end
You proved yourself in the group
with Apples,

00:02:59.078 --> 00:03:01.447 line:95%,end
and you proved your solo.

00:03:01.514 --> 00:03:02.982 line:5%,start
I knew I could get higher
in the pyramid,

00:03:03.049 --> 00:03:05.251 line:5%,start
because I did great last week.

00:03:05.318 --> 00:03:06.619 line:95%,end
ABBY: Maddie.

00:03:06.686 --> 00:03:08.121 line:95%,end
Maddie, I thought
you did a great job

00:03:08.188 --> 00:03:09.689 line:95%,end
in the group and your solo.

00:03:09.756 --> 00:03:11.457 line:95%,end
Well, keep working.

00:03:11.524 --> 00:03:13.259 line:95%,end
You need something to work for.

00:03:13.326 --> 00:03:15.662 line:95%,end
And on top of the pyramid this week,
Chloe.

00:03:15.728 --> 00:03:16.729 line:95%,end
(applause)

00:03:16.796 --> 00:03:18.097 line:95%,end
ABBY: <i>Chloe had to be</i>
<i>on top of the pyramid.</i>

00:03:18.164 --> 00:03:19.232 line:95%,end
<i>She was the overall high score winner,</i>

00:03:19.299 --> 00:03:22.268 line:95%,end
<i>and that's usually the person</i>
<i>that's in that key position.</i>

00:03:22.335 --> 00:03:25.438 line:95%,end
It will be, you know,
up to Chloe if she stays

00:03:25.505 --> 00:03:27.006 line:95%,end
<i>in that position or not.</i>

00:03:27.073 --> 00:03:29.842 line:95%,end
You did something out there,
you made your mother cry,


00:03:29.909 --> 00:03:31.044 line:95%,end
she was bawling.

00:03:31.110 --> 00:03:34.013 line:95%,end
Don't make me cry, make me smile.

00:03:34.080 --> 00:03:35.748 line:95%,end
I think this is a little hard on Melissa.

00:03:35.815 --> 00:03:37.450 line:95%,end
<i>Chloe is above Maddie on the pyramid.</i>

00:03:37.517 --> 00:03:39.452 line:95%,end
<i>So it's like celebration day.</i>

00:03:39.519 --> 00:03:40.920 line:95%,end
Ice cream for everyone.

00:03:40.987 --> 00:03:43.223 line:95%,end
ABBY:
This week in Hollywood Vibe, Chloe,

00:03:43.289 --> 00:03:44.924 line:95%,end
you will be doing a solo again.

00:03:44.991 --> 00:03:47.093 line:95%,end
Maddie, you will also be doing a solo.

00:03:47.160 --> 00:03:49.495 line:95%,end
And we're going to do a trio,

00:03:49.562 --> 00:03:53.967 line:95%,end
and the trio is going to be Chloe, Maddie,

00:03:54.767 --> 00:03:56.769 line:95%,end
and--

00:03:56.836 --> 00:03:59.639 line:95%,end
(tense music playing)

00:04:00.873 --> 00:04:02.141 line:95%,end
Kendall.

00:04:05.311 --> 00:04:08.948 line:5%,start
PAIGE: As a dancer,
I've been in this trio since I was four.

00:04:09.015 --> 00:04:10.216 line:95%,end
<i>I think I should be in the trio,</i>

00:04:10.283 --> 00:04:13.953 line:95%,end
<i>and I think because Miss Abby's mad</i>
<i>at Brooke and my mom</i>

00:04:14.020 --> 00:04:15.622 line:95%,end
that she's taking it out on me.

00:04:15.688 --> 00:04:18.358 line:95%,end
ABBY: Kendall, you stepped it up
from Apple's last week.

00:04:18.424 --> 00:04:23.029 line:95%,end
But now I need to see
if you can hang with Chloe and Maddie.

00:04:23.096 --> 00:04:25.698 line:95%,end
KELLY: <i>I am not mad because</i>
<i>Kendall was put in the dance.</i>

00:04:25.765 --> 00:04:27.800 line:5%,start
I know that Abby is doing it

00:04:27.867 --> 00:04:30.837 line:95%,end
<i>because she wants to hurt me</i>
<i>and hurt my kid.</i>

00:04:30.903 --> 00:04:33.006 line:95%,end
Let me talk about the group dance.

00:04:33.072 --> 00:04:35.441 line:95%,end
It's a contemporary lyrical routine.

00:04:35.508 --> 00:04:37.310 line:95%,end
I am putting art on the stage.

00:04:37.377 --> 00:04:40.980 line:95%,end
It's going to be about a bully.

00:04:41.047 --> 00:04:43.383 line:95%,end
MADDIE: <i>The group number this week</i>
<i>is about bullying,</i>

00:04:43.449 --> 00:04:47.920 line:5%,start
and I actually have got bullied
before on my bus.

00:04:47.987 --> 00:04:50.790 line:95%,end
And I've also seen a lot
of bullying at my school.

00:04:50.857 --> 00:04:53.526 line:95%,end
There needs to be somebody
that's the bully.

00:04:53.593 --> 00:04:57.497 line:5%,start
HOLLY: I think it's incredibly ironic
that Abby's choice of dance

00:04:57.563 --> 00:05:00.300 line:5%,start
is about bullying considering
her methods of teaching.

00:05:00.366 --> 00:05:02.869 line:95%,end
ABBY:
Nia, you are going to be the bully.

00:05:02.935 --> 00:05:04.771 line:95%,end
Somebody has to be the bad guy.

00:05:04.837 --> 00:05:05.772 line:95%,end
(laughter)

00:05:05.838 --> 00:05:07.106 line:95%,end
GIRL: I can't imagine that.

00:05:07.173 --> 00:05:08.708 line:95%,end
ABBY: But she's an actress,
she has to act.

00:05:08.775 --> 00:05:09.909 line:95%,end
WOMAN: She's right, it's acting.

00:05:09.976 --> 00:05:11.711 line:95%,end
ABBY: So you're going to be my bully.

00:05:11.778 --> 00:05:13.179 line:95%,end
-Yes?
-Okay.

00:05:13.246 --> 00:05:15.615 line:5%,start
I'm so happy, because this Abby chose me

00:05:15.682 --> 00:05:18.951 line:5%,start
to be the one that's starring
in the group dance this week.

00:05:19.018 --> 00:05:22.088 line:95%,end
You have to be big, and strong,
and tough, and nasty.

00:05:22.155 --> 00:05:24.624 line:95%,end
HOLLY: Nia finally gets a special part,

00:05:24.691 --> 00:05:27.126 line:95%,end
she gets a featured role,
and I'm happy for her.

00:05:27.193 --> 00:05:28.928 line:95%,end
Finally she gets a chance.

00:05:28.995 --> 00:05:33.099 line:95%,end
But I'm not happy with Nia
being selected to portray a bully.

00:05:33.166 --> 00:05:36.202 line:95%,end
That leaves me
with one more bit of news.

00:05:36.269 --> 00:05:38.104 line:95%,end
<i>I know that they're all assuming</i>
<i>that that's Brooke</i>

00:05:38.171 --> 00:05:41.174 line:5%,start
<i>underneath that piece of paper,</i>
<i>but it's not.</i>

00:05:41.240 --> 00:05:43.042 line:95%,end
I always have a trick up my sleeve.

00:05:44.444 --> 00:05:46.379 line:95%,end
(dramatic music playing)

00:05:46.446 --> 00:05:48.081 line:95%,end
I'm bringing in another member,

00:05:48.147 --> 00:05:50.350 line:95%,end
a strong dancer,

00:05:50.416 --> 00:05:51.617 line:95%,end
that can go up against our bully.

00:05:51.684 --> 00:05:54.153 line:95%,end
We were looking for one person.

00:05:54.220 --> 00:05:56.389 line:95%,end
Find her a spot--solo, duet, anything.

00:05:56.456 --> 00:05:57.290 line:95%,end
Give her something.

00:05:57.357 --> 00:05:59.726 line:95%,end
Please welcome Peyton.

00:05:59.792 --> 00:06:01.427 line:95%,end
(squealing)

00:06:01.494 --> 00:06:04.831 line:95%,end
(dramatic music playing)

00:06:04.897 --> 00:06:07.033 line:95%,end
-(squealing)
-GIRL: No.

00:06:09.902 --> 00:06:11.137 line:95%,end
<i>My name is Peyton.</i>

00:06:11.204 --> 00:06:13.639 line:5%,start
I'm 14 years old,
and I've been dancing at Abby's

00:06:13.706 --> 00:06:15.007 line:5%,start
for about four years.

00:06:16.242 --> 00:06:18.745 line:95%,end
<i>Not everybody is able to make</i>
<i>Abby Lee Dance Company's</i>

00:06:18.811 --> 00:06:20.146 line:95%,end
competition group.

00:06:20.213 --> 00:06:24.016 line:95%,end
So for me to be a part of it,
I was so excited.

00:06:24.083 --> 00:06:25.918 line:95%,end
Okay, girls. Enough, come on, come on.

00:06:25.985 --> 00:06:27.954 line:95%,end
JILL: <i>What is Peyton doing here?</i>

00:06:28.020 --> 00:06:29.889 line:95%,end
She's going to come in
and try to take this spot

00:06:29.956 --> 00:06:31.391 line:95%,end
right out from under Kendall.

00:06:31.457 --> 00:06:33.326 line:95%,end
I hate this whole idea.

00:06:33.393 --> 00:06:36.396 line:95%,end
ABBY: Peyton,
you finally have a place.

00:06:36.462 --> 00:06:38.698 line:95%,end
But you need to prove yourself.

00:06:38.765 --> 00:06:40.466 line:95%,end
You are on probation.

00:06:40.533 --> 00:06:42.168 line:95%,end
You are the new kid on the block.

00:06:42.235 --> 00:06:43.903 line:95%,end
It's a whole new ball game.

00:06:43.970 --> 00:06:47.473 line:95%,end
Without Brooke
there is only one spot open

00:06:47.540 --> 00:06:49.208 line:95%,end
on this competition team.

00:06:49.275 --> 00:06:52.111 line:95%,end
Kendall and Peyton
both want that spot.

00:06:52.178 --> 00:06:53.846 line:95%,end
Let's get ready to rehearse.

00:06:53.913 --> 00:06:55.982 line:95%,end
Moms, you're dismissed.

00:06:56.048 --> 00:06:57.683 line:5%,start
(upbeat music playing)


00:06:57.750 --> 00:07:00.453 line:5%,start
ABBY: Soutenu, outside
compass, chaines,

00:07:00.520 --> 00:07:02.688 line:95%,end
up, up, chaines, down, down.

00:07:02.755 --> 00:07:06.392 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: Chloe, Maddie, and Paige have had
a trio since they were four years old.

00:07:06.459 --> 00:07:07.860 line:95%,end
MELISSA: Undefeated, I have you.

00:07:07.927 --> 00:07:09.629 line:95%,end
-KELLY: Yes, we have never lost.
-Never.

00:07:09.695 --> 00:07:11.864 line:95%,end
And I just think that
that's really rotten

00:07:11.931 --> 00:07:13.466 line:95%,end
that Paige was pulled from that trio.

00:07:13.533 --> 00:07:15.601 line:95%,end
-I don't think she's replacing Paige.
-KELLY: Well, she did.

00:07:15.668 --> 00:07:16.669 line:95%,end
I honestly--

00:07:16.736 --> 00:07:17.937 line:95%,end
She just did.

00:07:18.004 --> 00:07:19.772 line:95%,end
CHRISTI:
<i>Jill's a little Pollyanna right now.</i>

00:07:19.839 --> 00:07:21.441 line:5%,start
She's like, oh, this is all so great.

00:07:21.507 --> 00:07:23.309 line:5%,start
Everybody gets a turn.
Well, you know what?

00:07:23.376 --> 00:07:24.377 line:95%,end
Not with the trio.

00:07:24.444 --> 00:07:25.845 line:95%,end
The trio is sort of something
that's untouchable,

00:07:25.912 --> 00:07:27.413 line:95%,end
you leave it alone.

00:07:27.480 --> 00:07:28.681 line:95%,end
Shove her forward.

00:07:28.748 --> 00:07:29.882 line:95%,end
Go.

00:07:29.949 --> 00:07:31.417 line:95%,end
(dramatic music playing)

00:07:31.484 --> 00:07:32.418 line:95%,end
Do you see what Nia's doing?

00:07:32.485 --> 00:07:33.786 line:95%,end
ABBY: Bigger, harder, let's go.

00:07:33.853 --> 00:07:35.721 line:95%,end
Push her.

00:07:35.788 --> 00:07:37.690 line:95%,end
<i>Every single night on the news,</i>

00:07:37.757 --> 00:07:40.393 line:95%,end
you hear something about bullying

00:07:40.460 --> 00:07:42.895 line:95%,end
and problems in our schools today.

00:07:42.962 --> 00:07:46.666 line:95%,end
And I think it's important
for the children as artists

00:07:46.732 --> 00:07:49.135 line:95%,end
<i>to convey that message to their audience.</i>

00:07:49.202 --> 00:07:50.303 line:95%,end
Push her.

00:07:50.369 --> 00:07:51.971 line:95%,end
MELISSA: And then she's probably
going to have to kick somebody.

00:07:52.038 --> 00:07:52.872 line:95%,end
(woman gasping)

00:07:52.939 --> 00:07:53.773 line:95%,end
Stick it in their face.

00:07:53.840 --> 00:07:54.941 line:95%,end
And then pull Kendall's ponytails.

00:07:55.007 --> 00:07:56.476 line:95%,end
ABBY: Keep working on it.

00:07:56.542 --> 00:07:58.311 line:95%,end
Oh, this is ridiculous.

00:07:58.377 --> 00:08:00.146 line:95%,end
The role of a dance mom is not easy.

00:08:00.213 --> 00:08:02.281 line:95%,end
Sometimes you have to make
really tough decisions,

00:08:02.348 --> 00:08:05.418 line:95%,end
<i>and this is one of those times.</i>

00:08:05.485 --> 00:08:07.286 line:95%,end
Nia was not going to portray the bully.

00:08:07.353 --> 00:08:09.388 line:95%,end
<i>There was no need for her</i>
<i>to have that role.</i>

00:08:09.455 --> 00:08:12.525 line:95%,end
<i>She can play lots of characters,</i>
<i>but she's not playing a bully.</i>

00:08:14.694 --> 00:08:16.562 line:95%,end
-What?
-I have a huge problem

00:08:16.629 --> 00:08:17.864 line:95%,end
with Nia portraying the bully.

00:08:20.166 --> 00:08:22.902 line:95%,end
I know you're going to say,
she's playing a character.

00:08:22.969 --> 00:08:24.504 line:95%,end
I finally give you a part, kid.

00:08:24.570 --> 00:08:25.872 line:95%,end
HOLLY: I know.
I want her to be a featured part.

00:08:25.938 --> 00:08:28.040 line:95%,end
I just want her to be a part--
I want her to be part of the dance.

00:08:28.107 --> 00:08:31.143 line:95%,end
At my school
there is a zero tolerance policy

00:08:31.210 --> 00:08:32.478 line:95%,end
regarding bullying.

00:08:32.545 --> 00:08:34.213 line:95%,end
I wish there was
a zero tolerance policy also

00:08:34.280 --> 00:08:35.848 line:95%,end
at the dance studio too.

00:08:35.915 --> 00:08:37.617 line:95%,end
Peyton, you're the bully.

00:08:37.683 --> 00:08:38.784 line:95%,end
Nia, you're not the bully.

00:08:38.851 --> 00:08:42.188 line:95%,end
NIA: <i>My mom didn't like the part</i>
<i>that I was doing in the dance,</i>

00:08:42.255 --> 00:08:45.157 line:95%,end
because it's a bully,
and I'm not a bully.

00:08:45.224 --> 00:08:46.759 line:95%,end
ABBY: You got a featured part
in a number,

00:08:46.826 --> 00:08:48.060 line:95%,end
and your mom took it away from you.

00:08:48.127 --> 00:08:49.629 line:95%,end
Not me.

00:08:49.695 --> 00:08:52.832 line:95%,end
She took a part away from her child.

00:08:52.899 --> 00:08:53.933 line:95%,end
I didn't.

00:08:54.000 --> 00:08:55.768 line:95%,end
HOLLY: <i>I want Nia to have a feature part.</i>

00:08:55.835 --> 00:08:57.303 line:95%,end
<i>I wanted her to be part of the dance.</i>

00:08:57.370 --> 00:08:59.839 line:95%,end
But I don't want her to have
that featured part.

00:08:59.906 --> 00:09:01.674 line:95%,end
Chloe, you're going to enter first.

00:09:01.741 --> 00:09:03.242 line:95%,end
Right there.

00:09:03.309 --> 00:09:05.711 line:95%,end
You're on the top of the pyramid,
don't push it.

00:09:05.778 --> 00:09:07.446 line:95%,end
I don't know why your mother doesn't
say you have confidence.

00:09:07.513 --> 00:09:09.348 line:95%,end
You are the cockiest kid
I've ever worked with.

00:09:09.415 --> 00:09:12.018 line:95%,end
CHRISTI:
Isn't it ironic that Abby's tactics

00:09:12.084 --> 00:09:15.721 line:95%,end
are very equivalent to bullying
in a dance about bullying.

00:09:15.788 --> 00:09:18.391 line:95%,end
I'm giving you both legs straight,
and you're doing one bent.

00:09:18.457 --> 00:09:19.825 line:95%,end
Do you understand?

00:09:19.892 --> 00:09:21.961 line:95%,end
She just doesn't have a brain
in her head, move in.

00:09:22.028 --> 00:09:24.630 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: <i>I have to be very careful</i>
<i>of the battles I pick with Abby,</i>

00:09:24.697 --> 00:09:26.699 line:95%,end
<i>because Abby doesn't like me.</i>

00:09:26.766 --> 00:09:29.135 line:95%,end
<i>She's made that perfectly clear.</i>

00:09:29.201 --> 00:09:30.703 line:95%,end
But when I see Chloe starting to cry,

00:09:30.770 --> 00:09:34.473 line:95%,end
and I see the tears actually on her shirt
of her dance wear,

00:09:34.540 --> 00:09:36.609 line:95%,end
I'm thinking, oh God,
what is going on in there?

00:09:36.676 --> 00:09:38.377 line:95%,end
She's an evil bitch.

00:09:39.512 --> 00:09:41.347 line:95%,end
Chloe's crying.

00:09:41.414 --> 00:09:43.482 line:95%,end
ABBY: I expect more from you.

00:09:43.549 --> 00:09:45.284 line:95%,end
You should know
what's straight legs are.

00:09:45.351 --> 00:09:47.286 line:95%,end
And you ignore me,
and you just keep going.

00:09:47.353 --> 00:09:50.056 line:95%,end
CHLOE: <i>I'm a little upset,</i>
<i>because I didn't understand</i>

00:09:50.122 --> 00:09:52.191 line:5%,start
what Miss Abby was saying
to me for choreography.

00:09:52.258 --> 00:09:55.328 line:95%,end
ABBY: You're not a choreographer,
don't start being one.

00:09:55.394 --> 00:09:56.796 line:95%,end
CHLOE: And she yelled at me,

00:09:56.862 --> 00:09:59.332 line:95%,end
<i>because I was doing another thing.</i>

00:09:59.398 --> 00:10:01.334 line:95%,end
<i>She was like, you're choreographing,</i>

00:10:01.400 --> 00:10:03.469 line:95%,end
<i>and I really wasn't trying to choreograph.</i>

00:10:03.536 --> 00:10:05.771 line:95%,end
I just didn't know what she meant.

00:10:05.838 --> 00:10:06.839 line:95%,end
She'll come out.

00:10:06.906 --> 00:10:08.307 line:95%,end
KELLY: She isn't going to come out.

00:10:08.374 --> 00:10:09.742 line:95%,end
Do you want to go down and see?

00:10:09.809 --> 00:10:11.978 line:95%,end
-KELLY: Abby will kill her.
-I can't walk in that room.

00:10:12.044 --> 00:10:13.980 line:95%,end
Well, Chloe isn't
going to walk out.

00:10:14.046 --> 00:10:15.314 line:95%,end
-HOLLY: Go get her.
-KELLY: Then she'll yelled at more.

00:10:15.381 --> 00:10:16.682 line:95%,end
ABBY: You're on the top of the pyramid.

00:10:16.749 --> 00:10:17.783 line:95%,end
Suck it up.

00:10:17.850 --> 00:10:20.353 line:95%,end
The next kid's on speed dial
to come to the studio.


00:10:23.122 --> 00:10:25.091 line:5%,start
(dramatic music playing)

00:10:25.157 --> 00:10:27.693 line:5%,start
-(doorbell)
-(screeches)

00:10:27.760 --> 00:10:29.929 line:5%,start
KELLY: <i>Brooke made</i>
<i>the cheerleading team,</i>

00:10:29.996 --> 00:10:32.965 line:5%,start
and I thought it was a good idea
to have all the girls

00:10:33.032 --> 00:10:36.002 line:95%,end
<i>come to my house and have a party</i>
<i>to congratulate Brooke.</i>

00:10:36.068 --> 00:10:37.269 line:95%,end
Oh, I love you.

00:10:37.336 --> 00:10:38.170 line:95%,end
MACKENZIE: <i>I miss Brooke.</i>

00:10:38.237 --> 00:10:40.906 line:5%,start
I miss having her here
on the dance team.

00:10:40.973 --> 00:10:43.643 line:95%,end
Is cheerleading different than dance?

00:10:44.276 --> 00:10:47.046 line:95%,end
Is the teacher nicer than Miss Abby?

00:10:47.113 --> 00:10:49.715 line:95%,end
PAIGE: Brooke, show us something
that you learned from cheer.

00:10:49.782 --> 00:10:51.651 line:95%,end
Ready? Okay.

00:10:52.318 --> 00:10:53.519 line:95%,end
(girls giggling)

00:10:53.586 --> 00:10:56.088 line:95%,end
PAIGE: Two, four, six, eight,
who do we appreciate?

00:10:56.155 --> 00:10:57.289 line:95%,end
Nia! Nia!

00:10:57.356 --> 00:10:58.357 line:95%,end
-Go Nia!
-(giggling)

00:10:58.424 --> 00:10:59.425 line:95%,end
I miss you, Brooke.

00:10:59.492 --> 00:11:00.893 line:95%,end
You're like--you're, like,
the best friend ever.

00:11:00.960 --> 00:11:02.495 line:95%,end
GIRL: You're my sister.

00:11:03.896 --> 00:11:05.531 line:95%,end
BROOKE: <i>I really miss the girls.</i>

00:11:05.598 --> 00:11:07.767 line:5%,start
They're pretty much a part of my family,

00:11:07.833 --> 00:11:09.902 line:95%,end
and I feel like I haven't seen them
in years.

00:11:09.969 --> 00:11:11.637 line:95%,end
Do you wish you were coming
with us this week?

00:11:11.704 --> 00:11:14.340 line:95%,end
No, because I'm going to a football game.

00:11:14.407 --> 00:11:16.342 line:95%,end
Do you want to come back to dance?

00:11:16.409 --> 00:11:17.309 line:95%,end
I don't know.

00:11:19.545 --> 00:11:20.880 line:5%,start
ABBY: Tuck, ball change.

00:11:20.946 --> 00:11:22.415 line:5%,start
Plie and push.

00:11:22.481 --> 00:11:23.816 line:5%,start
MADDIE: I really want to dance around

00:11:23.883 --> 00:11:26.118 line:5%,start
and beat Chloe and get back
to the top of the pyramid.

00:11:26.185 --> 00:11:30.423 line:5%,start
ABBY: Five and six, seven and eight.

00:11:30.489 --> 00:11:32.458 line:5%,start
I think Maddie's ready
for the challenge

00:11:32.525 --> 00:11:35.194 line:95%,end
<i>of going up against me,</i>
<i>because she's a very strong dancer.</i>

00:11:35.261 --> 00:11:37.396 line:95%,end
So I hope I do great at my solo.

00:11:40.633 --> 00:11:43.302 line:5%,start
(tense music playing)

00:11:45.304 --> 00:11:46.472 line:5%,start
Peyton's things working out fine.

00:11:46.539 --> 00:11:48.808 line:95%,end
<i>She, again, is a natural-born leader,</i>

00:11:48.874 --> 00:11:51.110 line:95%,end
<i>so she's taking the place</i>
<i>of Brooke rather well.</i>

00:11:51.177 --> 00:11:53.212 line:95%,end
She counts the music, she gets it.

00:11:53.279 --> 00:11:55.147 line:95%,end
Her and Maddie
have worked together before,

00:11:55.214 --> 00:11:57.016 line:95%,end
<i>so they're doing some partner work.</i>

00:11:57.817 --> 00:11:59.985 line:95%,end
JILL: That is amazing,
because they're all different ages,

00:12:00.052 --> 00:12:01.921 line:95%,end
but they're all the same height.

00:12:01.987 --> 00:12:03.222 line:95%,end
And then we got big Peyton.

00:12:03.289 --> 00:12:06.659 line:5%,start
My name is Leslie,
and I've been in Abby's for four years.

00:12:06.726 --> 00:12:10.096 line:95%,end
JILL: I just really hope that Peyton
doesn't look too big.

00:12:10.162 --> 00:12:12.798 line:5%,start
I don't understand
why Peyton is back in the picture.

00:12:12.865 --> 00:12:16.202 line:95%,end
Peyton's too big, she's going
to stand out like a sore thumb.

00:12:16.268 --> 00:12:18.838 line:95%,end
<i>Now, Kendall fits right into this group.</i>

00:12:18.904 --> 00:12:20.639 line:95%,end
LESLIE: <i>Call bias, I'm her mother.</i>

00:12:20.706 --> 00:12:22.742 line:95%,end
I think she's the better dancer.

00:12:22.808 --> 00:12:25.111 line:95%,end
I'm going to say she's a better dancer
than Kendall in this style.

00:12:25.177 --> 00:12:28.114 line:95%,end
I do understand that Jill
would be uncomfortable.

00:12:28.180 --> 00:12:30.282 line:95%,end
<i>I'm going to let her know</i>
<i>that I think Peyton</i>

00:12:30.349 --> 00:12:31.717 line:95%,end
should be on this team
and not her daughter.

00:12:31.784 --> 00:12:33.686 line:95%,end
I've put more time in than she has.

00:12:33.753 --> 00:12:36.388 line:95%,end
I think Peyton being picked
to be showcased

00:12:36.455 --> 00:12:37.790 line:95%,end
as the bully in the lead--

00:12:37.857 --> 00:12:39.291 line:95%,end
But she got that by default.

00:12:39.358 --> 00:12:41.827 line:95%,end
Well, Jill, they could have given it
to Kendall,

00:12:41.894 --> 00:12:43.028 line:95%,end
but no, they gave it to Peyton,

00:12:43.095 --> 00:12:44.497 line:95%,end
and I think Abby made the right choice.

00:12:45.397 --> 00:12:48.234 line:95%,end
ABBY: I don't know Jill well enough
to guesstimate

00:12:48.300 --> 00:12:50.035 line:95%,end
how she's going to handle Leslie,

00:12:50.102 --> 00:12:51.604 line:95%,end
but I do know Leslie.

00:12:51.670 --> 00:12:53.506 line:95%,end
And I'll tell you what,

00:12:53.572 --> 00:12:55.641 line:95%,end
Jill better get a own baseball bat out.

00:12:55.708 --> 00:12:58.010 line:95%,end
She originally picked Kendall
over Peyton

00:12:58.077 --> 00:12:59.378 line:95%,end
to dance with this group,

00:12:59.445 --> 00:13:04.016 line:95%,end
and my fear is now that we need an extra,
she's putting Peyton in.

00:13:04.083 --> 00:13:06.085 line:95%,end
<i>Originally, she didn't want Peyton.</i>

00:13:06.152 --> 00:13:08.854 line:95%,end
There had to have been
a reason behind it,

00:13:08.921 --> 00:13:11.690 line:95%,end
and I hope that doesn't hurt the group
in the long run.

00:13:11.757 --> 00:13:13.926 line:95%,end
That's all. I know she's a good dancer.

00:13:13.993 --> 00:13:15.594 line:95%,end
Then why do you think they put in it

00:13:15.661 --> 00:13:17.062 line:95%,end
when they could have picked somebody else?

00:13:17.129 --> 00:13:19.598 line:95%,end
Because you reamed her out, and said,
you better find a spot for her.

00:13:19.665 --> 00:13:20.533 line:95%,end
LESLIE: And who am?

00:13:20.599 --> 00:13:21.667 line:95%,end
Who am I?

00:13:21.734 --> 00:13:23.502 line:95%,end
Why does my--why is my word gold?

00:13:23.569 --> 00:13:25.037 line:95%,end
You said before you had Abby's ear,

00:13:25.104 --> 00:13:27.039 line:95%,end
-and I actually I do commend you on that.
-I do have Abby's ear.

00:13:27.106 --> 00:13:28.274 line:95%,end
That's exactly why.

00:13:29.508 --> 00:13:30.543 line:95%,end
We'll see.

00:13:30.609 --> 00:13:32.978 line:95%,end
I'm a little concerned right now
about Leslie,

00:13:33.045 --> 00:13:35.014 line:95%,end
because I know
at the open audition,

00:13:35.080 --> 00:13:36.582 line:95%,end
<i>she had a blowout with Abby.</i>

00:13:36.649 --> 00:13:41.053 line:95%,end
And I know that she asked Abby
to do whatever she had to do

00:13:41.120 --> 00:13:44.056 line:95%,end
<i>to get Peyton on with this dance team.</i>

00:13:44.123 --> 00:13:45.524 line:95%,end
Put that big bully in there.

00:13:45.591 --> 00:13:47.293 line:95%,end
(laughter)

00:13:47.359 --> 00:13:48.828 line:95%,end
-JILL: (indistinct)
-Like mother, like daughter.

00:13:50.496 --> 00:13:53.265 line:95%,end
She's a big bully, not just a bully.

00:13:53.332 --> 00:13:54.733 line:95%,end
More person to watch.

00:13:54.800 --> 00:13:57.937 line:5%,start
(upbeat music playing)

00:13:58.003 --> 00:14:00.072 line:95%,end
ABBY: <i>A trio is one</i>
<i>of the most difficult numbers to do</i>

00:14:00.139 --> 00:14:01.574 line:95%,end
<i>because of spacing.</i>

00:14:01.640 --> 00:14:03.275 line:95%,end
You rehearse those groups
over and over

00:14:03.342 --> 00:14:05.711 line:95%,end
so you have spatial awareness
of where everybody is.

00:14:05.778 --> 00:14:07.079 line:95%,end
Paige, are you running the music?

00:14:07.813 --> 00:14:10.950 line:95%,end
<i>I think that Kendall is doing a great job.</i>

00:14:11.016 --> 00:14:14.687 line:95%,end
<i>I don't know if Paige would</i>
<i>have been a better choice or not</i>

00:14:14.753 --> 00:14:18.224 line:95%,end
given the fact that
it's a very difficult choreography


00:14:18.290 --> 00:14:19.291 line:95%,end
count wise.

00:14:19.358 --> 00:14:22.127 line:95%,end
Six, seven, and eight.

00:14:22.194 --> 00:14:25.331 line:95%,end
Whoa, whoa, whoa, eight.

00:14:27.099 --> 00:14:28.167 line:95%,end
That feels awkward.

00:14:28.234 --> 00:14:31.237 line:95%,end
<i>I think Paige would have been Darling</i>
<i>as an actress,</i>

00:14:31.303 --> 00:14:34.006 line:95%,end
but her ability to comprehend
quickly and remember

00:14:34.073 --> 00:14:35.808 line:95%,end
<i>is not to where Kendall's is.</i>

00:14:36.709 --> 00:14:38.043 line:95%,end
JILL: <i>Poor Paige? Where's Paige at?</i>

00:14:38.110 --> 00:14:39.979 line:95%,end
Uh-oh, I think
she's running the music, Kelly.

00:14:41.213 --> 00:14:43.215 line:95%,end
That is like, such (bleep).

00:14:43.282 --> 00:14:45.084 line:95%,end
KELLY: <i>So Abby's running</i>
<i>practice for the trio,</i>

00:14:45.150 --> 00:14:47.453 line:95%,end
<i>she has Paige running the music.</i>

00:14:47.519 --> 00:14:49.521 line:95%,end
First of all,
you replaced her with Kendall.

00:14:49.588 --> 00:14:51.557 line:95%,end
<i>And now you have her sitting in there</i>

00:14:51.624 --> 00:14:53.792 line:95%,end
<i>watching her learn the choreography</i>

00:14:53.859 --> 00:14:56.462 line:95%,end
<i>and having her playing the music</i>
<i>while they're learning it.</i>

00:14:56.528 --> 00:14:58.964 line:95%,end
Like, why would you do that
to a 10-year-old kid?

00:14:59.031 --> 00:15:00.132 line:95%,end
It's just wrong.

00:15:00.199 --> 00:15:02.902 line:95%,end
There's no reason my daughter
should be sitting in that room

00:15:02.968 --> 00:15:04.403 line:95%,end
<i>playing music.</i>

00:15:04.470 --> 00:15:07.006 line:95%,end
She's just doing it to hurt her.

00:15:08.440 --> 00:15:10.776 line:95%,end
LESLIE: I love when Abby dances
with the group. Look at that.

00:15:10.843 --> 00:15:12.311 line:95%,end
I know, it cracks me up.
Okay, I'm going to look--

00:15:12.378 --> 00:15:13.846 line:95%,end
I would love to see her do
one turn though.

00:15:13.913 --> 00:15:14.747 line:95%,end
-(indistinct)
-Ha!

00:15:14.813 --> 00:15:16.015 line:95%,end
On a pigeon toe.

00:15:16.081 --> 00:15:18.484 line:95%,end
KELLY: (yells) I don't think
she could do something on one foot.

00:15:18.550 --> 00:15:20.019 line:95%,end
Her leg can't hold up her body.

00:15:20.085 --> 00:15:22.354 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: Can you imagine that ankle?
It would be screaming stop!

00:15:22.421 --> 00:15:23.722 line:95%,end
(laughter)

00:15:23.789 --> 00:15:25.090 line:95%,end
I don't think that would work.

00:15:27.159 --> 00:15:29.662 line:95%,end
(soft music playing)

00:15:30.362 --> 00:15:32.564 line:95%,end
LESLIE: <i>I was very surprised</i>
<i>that Abby called me</i>

00:15:32.631 --> 00:15:34.700 line:95%,end
and asked Peyton to fill in for Brooke.

00:15:34.767 --> 00:15:38.070 line:95%,end
<i>And I knew when I got back that I really</i>
<i>should get together with the moms.</i>

00:15:38.137 --> 00:15:40.773 line:95%,end
<i>And I just wanted to talk with them</i>
<i>and have coffee and lunch</i>

00:15:40.839 --> 00:15:43.108 line:95%,end
<i>and just see how they felt</i>
<i>about Peyton joining their team.</i>

00:15:43.175 --> 00:15:46.679 line:95%,end
I am so excited, and I wanted
to let you know how excited I am

00:15:46.745 --> 00:15:50.516 line:95%,end
that Peyton is actually competing
with this dance team now.

00:15:50.582 --> 00:15:53.485 line:5%,start
CHRISTI: I'm a little skeptical why Leslie
wants to invite us out for coffee.

00:15:53.552 --> 00:15:55.521 line:5%,start
I've known Leslie for a long time,

00:15:56.422 --> 00:15:59.658 line:95%,end
and there's usually
an underhanded motive behind Leslie.

00:15:59.725 --> 00:16:01.327 line:95%,end
And Brooke wants to cheerlead.

00:16:01.393 --> 00:16:03.595 line:95%,end
Why do you get up every single day

00:16:03.662 --> 00:16:06.632 line:95%,end
and drive to that studio
if this lady tortures you?

00:16:06.699 --> 00:16:08.334 line:95%,end
I just need that answer.

00:16:08.400 --> 00:16:10.736 line:95%,end
My daughter, Paige,
wants to be there with her friends.

00:16:10.803 --> 00:16:12.304 line:95%,end
Okay, Christi, let's go to you.

00:16:12.371 --> 00:16:13.372 line:95%,end
Why are you there then?

00:16:13.439 --> 00:16:14.974 line:95%,end
-If she had been--
-You know what, Leslie?

00:16:15.040 --> 00:16:16.408 line:95%,end
That's between me and my daughter.

00:16:16.475 --> 00:16:18.610 line:95%,end
I don't feel like I have to sit here
and answer to people why.

00:16:18.677 --> 00:16:21.347 line:95%,end
You don't have to answer,
but you do complain about it a lot.

00:16:21.413 --> 00:16:22.314 line:95%,end
Yes.

00:16:22.381 --> 00:16:25.551 line:5%,start
MELISSA: Leslie kind of likes
to take charge of every situation.

00:16:25.617 --> 00:16:27.853 line:5%,start
It's just her--it's just her way.

00:16:27.920 --> 00:16:29.888 line:95%,end
If it comes down to it
and Brooke does come back,

00:16:29.955 --> 00:16:32.524 line:95%,end
I think Brooke and Peyton
should be able to say before Kendall.

00:16:32.591 --> 00:16:33.892 line:95%,end
You are new.

00:16:33.959 --> 00:16:36.128 line:95%,end
You're on probation.
Peyton should not be on probation.

00:16:38.097 --> 00:16:39.465 line:95%,end
Hi.

00:16:39.531 --> 00:16:41.266 line:95%,end
(interposing voices)

00:16:42.701 --> 00:16:43.936 line:95%,end
Thanks for coming.

00:16:44.703 --> 00:16:47.039 line:95%,end
What did Nia have to say
last night about it?

00:16:47.106 --> 00:16:48.107 line:95%,end
She was upset.

00:16:48.173 --> 00:16:50.042 line:95%,end
I understand why I shouldn't be the bully,

00:16:50.109 --> 00:16:52.077 line:95%,end
