(suspenseful music playing)

00:35:29.026 --> 00:35:32.697 line:95%,end
We have a really nice
camaraderie amongst the girls here,

00:35:32.763 --> 00:35:34.332 line:95%,end
but we don't critique each other.

00:35:34.932 --> 00:35:37.969 line:95%,end
I ask you how you felt about you,
not in comparison

00:35:38.035 --> 00:35:40.271 line:95%,end
to everyone else,
just about your performance.

00:35:40.338 --> 00:35:42.940 line:95%,end
-So everybody was perfect but Peyton?
-No.

00:35:43.007 --> 00:35:44.375 line:95%,end
LESLIE: You didn't critique
one other person.

00:35:44.442 --> 00:35:46.511 line:95%,end
I don't need to.

00:35:46.577 --> 00:35:48.045 line:95%,end
Peyton did for me. (laughs)

00:35:48.112 --> 00:35:50.515 line:95%,end
I don't think there is an apology
to get give the group.

00:35:50.581 --> 00:35:54.519 line:95%,end
She said it, it's out there,
and it was wrong, and it was bad.

00:35:54.585 --> 00:35:57.922 line:95%,end
It will take years to regain their trust.

00:35:58.789 --> 00:36:03.094 line:95%,end
<i>These are her friends,</i>
<i>these are her comrades, this is her team.</i>

00:36:03.161 --> 00:36:05.129 line:95%,end
She shouldn't belittle others.

00:36:05.196 --> 00:36:06.430 line:95%,end
That's my job.

00:36:06.497 --> 00:36:08.699 line:95%,end
(dramatic music playing)

00:36:08.766 --> 00:36:12.637 line:5%,start
ANNOUNCER: <i>Ladies and gentlemen,</i>
<i>welcome to awards presentation.</i>

00:36:12.703 --> 00:36:13.871 line:95%,end
(cheering and applause)

00:36:13.938 --> 00:36:15.873 line:95%,end
ABBY: <i>I'm always nervous at a competition.</i>

00:36:15.940 --> 00:36:18.743 line:95%,end
<i>I have a group without</i>
<i>one of their key players,</i>

00:36:18.809 --> 00:36:21.612 line:95%,end
<i>I have a new member</i>
<i>that's a foot taller than everybody else.</i>

00:36:21.679 --> 00:36:23.447 line:95%,end
<i>I have another kid</i>
<i>that's still on probation</i>

00:36:23.514 --> 00:36:25.283 line:95%,end
that keeps making mistakes.

00:36:25.349 --> 00:36:26.951 line:95%,end
Yes, of course I'm nervous.

00:36:27.018 --> 00:36:29.587 line:95%,end
ANNOUNCER: <i>Junior solo, third place--</i>

00:36:29.654 --> 00:36:34.926 line:95%,end
<i>third place trophy going to act</i>
<i>number four, baby, I'm A Star.</i>

00:36:36.928 --> 00:36:41.132 line:95%,end
<i>Second place goes to act number 6, Pray.</i>


00:36:41.199 --> 00:36:43.968 line:95%,end
(cheering and applause)

00:36:44.035 --> 00:36:48.472 line:95%,end
ANNOUNCER: <i>And the first place winner,</i>
<i>junior solo division</i>

00:36:48.539 --> 00:36:52.677 line:95%,end
<i>is act number 12, The Girl I Want To Be.</i>

00:36:52.743 --> 00:36:54.111 line:95%,end
(applause)

00:36:54.178 --> 00:36:55.746 line:95%,end
ABBY: <i>Maddie won her division</i>

00:36:55.813 --> 00:36:57.548 line:95%,end
<i>which there was no doubt in my mind</i>

00:36:57.615 --> 00:36:59.450 line:95%,end
that she was the strongest thing there.

00:36:59.517 --> 00:37:01.385 line:95%,end
<i>I gave Chloe the opportunity.</i>

00:37:01.452 --> 00:37:03.788 line:95%,end
<i>This was her week,</i>
<i>she was at the top of the pyramid,</i>

00:37:03.854 --> 00:37:05.690 line:95%,end
<i>and she didn't even place.</i>

00:37:05.756 --> 00:37:07.225 line:95%,end
<i>She definitely needs to be reminded,</i>

00:37:07.291 --> 00:37:09.026 line:95%,end
<i>you're only as good</i>
<i>as your last performance.</i>

00:37:09.093 --> 00:37:12.830 line:95%,end
ANNOUNCER:
<i>On to the junior duo, trio division.</i>

00:37:12.897 --> 00:37:15.866 line:95%,end
<i>First place trophy over all goes to...</i>

00:37:17.602 --> 00:37:20.104 line:95%,end
<i>act number 21, My Boyfriend's Back.</i>

00:37:20.171 --> 00:37:22.540 line:95%,end
(cheering and applause)

00:37:22.607 --> 00:37:24.208 line:95%,end
<i>Congratulations.</i>

00:37:24.275 --> 00:37:28.446 line:95%,end
KELLY: <i>I have to admit,</i>
<i>when the trio did not place first,</i>

00:37:28.512 --> 00:37:30.181 line:5%,start
I was kind of relieved.

00:37:30.248 --> 00:37:33.651 line:95%,end
<i>I mean, their trio with Maddie,</i>
<i>Paige, and Chloe</i>

00:37:33.718 --> 00:37:37.221 line:95%,end
has always won first place everywhere.

00:37:37.288 --> 00:37:39.857 line:95%,end
<i>Now I can always say,</i>
<i>you should stick with what works.</i>

00:37:39.924 --> 00:37:40.925 line:95%,end
(laughs)

00:37:40.992 --> 00:37:44.695 line:95%,end
ANNOUNCER: <i>Intermediate</i>
<i>Modern Small Group, are you ready?</i>

00:37:44.762 --> 00:37:45.763 line:95%,end
(cheering and applause)

00:37:45.830 --> 00:37:49.567 line:95%,end
<i>Second place goes to</i>
<i>"I Love Rock And Roll."</i>

00:37:52.770 --> 00:37:54.505 line:95%,end
-This is us.
-ANNOUNCER: <i>First place goes to...</i>

00:37:56.340 --> 00:37:57.708 line:95%,end
<i>"Bad Time Girls."</i>

00:37:57.775 --> 00:37:59.810 line:95%,end
(cheering and applause)

00:37:59.877 --> 00:38:01.646 line:95%,end
<i>Nice job.</i>

00:38:01.712 --> 00:38:04.548 line:95%,end
ABBY: The group dance also
did not win their category.

00:38:04.615 --> 00:38:08.319 line:95%,end
<i>I thought for sure</i>
<i>with the level of difficulty</i>

00:38:08.386 --> 00:38:10.454 line:95%,end
that they were going to win that,
and they didn't.

00:38:10.521 --> 00:38:12.857 line:95%,end
<i>So either the judges didn't get it,</i>

00:38:12.923 --> 00:38:15.660 line:95%,end
maybe they thought it was inappropriate,
I don't know.

00:38:16.427 --> 00:38:17.862 line:95%,end
Hello.

00:38:17.928 --> 00:38:19.497 line:95%,end
KID: Hello.

00:38:19.563 --> 00:38:20.398 line:95%,end
ABBY: Chloe...

00:38:20.464 --> 00:38:22.400 line:95%,end
(dramatic music playing)

00:38:22.466 --> 00:38:24.802 line:95%,end
Remember, I told you,
getting on top of that pyramid

00:38:24.869 --> 00:38:26.804 line:95%,end
is one thing, staying there's another.

00:38:26.871 --> 00:38:28.539 line:95%,end
No matter who your competition is,

00:38:28.606 --> 00:38:30.141 line:95%,end
no matter how long they've been doing it,

00:38:30.207 --> 00:38:32.410 line:95%,end
doesn't matter
if you're in that age category,

00:38:32.476 --> 00:38:34.245 line:95%,end
I want you to win that age category.

00:38:34.312 --> 00:38:36.380 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: <i>It's so funny,</i>
<i>because Chloe finally earned her way</i>

00:38:36.447 --> 00:38:39.317 line:5%,start
to the top of the pyramid,
and Abby has said some things to her

00:38:39.383 --> 00:38:41.118 line:95%,end
<i>that are so out of line.</i>

00:38:41.185 --> 00:38:43.521 line:95%,end
<i>I've never heard her say</i>
<i>those things to Maddie.</i>

00:38:44.221 --> 00:38:45.723 line:95%,end
But there's no favoritism.

00:38:47.692 --> 00:38:51.495 line:95%,end
ABBY: So Peyton,
how about that overinflated ego, huh?

00:38:52.063 --> 00:38:54.098 line:95%,end
This group's been winning,
winning, winning, winning.

00:38:54.165 --> 00:38:55.466 line:95%,end
Do you think they lost because of her?

00:38:55.533 --> 00:38:57.001 line:95%,end
I don't know, I don't know.

00:38:57.068 --> 00:38:59.036 line:95%,end
I'll have to read the judge's comments

00:38:59.103 --> 00:39:01.572 line:95%,end
and listen to the critiques
and see what they say.

00:39:01.639 --> 00:39:04.075 line:95%,end
Is she going to be able to dance
with the team again?

00:39:04.141 --> 00:39:05.076 line:95%,end
ABBY: I don't know.

00:39:05.142 --> 00:39:09.380 line:95%,end
I don't think what she did on stage
really is what my concern is.

00:39:09.447 --> 00:39:11.415 line:95%,end
It was coming back to the dressing room

00:39:11.482 --> 00:39:13.517 line:95%,end
and saying that she was fabulous
and everybody else stunk.

00:39:13.584 --> 00:39:14.919 line:95%,end
You know what, you flustered her.

00:39:14.985 --> 00:39:16.253 line:95%,end
She didn't mean it like that.

00:39:16.320 --> 00:39:17.822 line:95%,end
You're talking to your 14-year-old.

00:39:17.888 --> 00:39:19.323 line:95%,end
If you want to fight with somebody,

00:39:19.390 --> 00:39:20.758 line:95%,end
then you fight with me, her mother.

00:39:20.825 --> 00:39:22.426 line:95%,end
ABBY: It's not about fighting, Leslie.

00:39:22.493 --> 00:39:24.528 line:95%,end
If you can't say anything nice,
don't say anything at all.

00:39:24.595 --> 00:39:26.897 line:95%,end
But it's different.
People are paying me for my opinion.

00:39:26.964 --> 00:39:29.233 line:95%,end
So you are still on probation.

00:39:29.300 --> 00:39:31.268 line:95%,end
You know, Peyton's sassy little mouth

00:39:31.335 --> 00:39:35.973 line:95%,end
may have just ruined her chances
of getting off probation.

00:39:36.040 --> 00:39:38.976 line:95%,end
Maybe even getting on
this competition team.

00:39:39.043 --> 00:39:42.313 line:95%,end
-Abby's really mad at Peyton.
-LESLIE: Why?

00:39:42.380 --> 00:39:45.716 line:95%,end
HOLLY: Because of the way it came out
Peyton was talking about

00:39:45.783 --> 00:39:47.251 line:95%,end
the rest of the group dance

00:39:47.318 --> 00:39:49.854 line:95%,end
and her performance in comparison
to everyone else.

00:39:49.920 --> 00:39:52.923 line:95%,end
I will speak for myself, I took it
the same way the Abby said it.

00:39:52.990 --> 00:39:55.926 line:95%,end
Wait, wait, and then she apologized,
then you're still saying this to me?

00:39:55.993 --> 00:39:57.561 line:95%,end
Are you going to let me finish my comment?

00:39:57.628 --> 00:39:59.563 line:95%,end
Well, because I'm pissed off, that's why.

00:39:59.630 --> 00:40:01.732 line:95%,end
You don't accept apologies
from a 14-year-old?

00:40:01.799 --> 00:40:03.934 line:95%,end
I did accept her apology.

00:40:04.001 --> 00:40:05.603 line:95%,end
-But--
-No, no, no, no.

00:40:05.669 --> 00:40:07.304 line:95%,end
There's a lot of enabling going on.

00:40:07.371 --> 00:40:09.240 line:95%,end
Somebody shut you down,
and you can't handle it.

00:40:09.306 --> 00:40:10.441 line:95%,end
CHRISTI:
You aren't shutting me down, Leslie.

00:40:10.508 --> 00:40:11.475 line:95%,end
Yes, I did.

00:40:11.542 --> 00:40:13.744 line:95%,end
Ladies, I'm standing outside

00:40:13.811 --> 00:40:15.112 line:95%,end
with a dance teacher
that's a friend of mine,

00:40:15.179 --> 00:40:16.881 line:95%,end
and I can hear every word you're saying.

00:40:16.947 --> 00:40:17.982 line:95%,end
I'm still upset, Abby.

00:40:18.048 --> 00:40:19.583 line:95%,end
I know, but Leslie, you know what?

00:40:19.650 --> 00:40:21.085 line:95%,end
Your daughter's 14 years old.

00:40:21.152 --> 00:40:23.354 line:95%,end
You say that she's a grown up,
she's this, she's that.

00:40:23.421 --> 00:40:24.822 line:95%,end
She has a smart mouth on her,

00:40:24.889 --> 00:40:26.657 line:95%,end
you need to dig your
fingernails into her back

00:40:26.724 --> 00:40:28.159 line:95%,end
-and tell her to shut her mouth.
-Okay, stop.

00:40:28.225 --> 00:40:31.228 line:95%,end
Did you not put her on the spot
that brought her to that point

00:40:31.295 --> 00:40:33.364 line:95%,end
where she said something wrong
and apologize to you?

00:40:33.431 --> 00:40:36.801 line:95%,end
You did not put her on this team
because of her comment.

00:40:36.867 --> 00:40:38.235 line:95%,end
That's what I want to know.

00:40:38.302 --> 00:40:40.137 line:95%,end
-Yes.
-Then that's a shame.

00:40:40.204 --> 00:40:42.740 line:95%,end
Shame on you, and I hope
you feel better

00:40:42.807 --> 00:40:44.275 line:95%,end
-laying your head down on your pillow.
-No shame on me.

00:40:44.341 --> 00:40:45.342 line:5%,start
Don't shame on me.

00:40:45.409 --> 00:40:46.677 line:5%,start
LESLIE: You gonna
kick her off to the curb?

00:40:46.744 --> 00:40:48.846 line:5%,start
You don't walk into a dressing room
with a whole group of people

00:40:48.913 --> 00:40:51.282 line:5%,start
and say, I was fabulous,
and you all weren't.

00:40:51.348 --> 00:40:53.184 line:5%,start
-It's ridiculous.
-LESLIE: No, you pick--

00:40:53.250 --> 00:40:54.452 line:5%,start
you let her daughter off probation.

00:40:54.518 --> 00:40:55.619 line:5%,start
-That's why.
-You don't need to be here.

00:40:55.686 --> 00:40:58.989 line:5%,start
You said, you can find a dance
to put her in, I did.

00:40:59.056 --> 00:41:01.058 line:5%,start
If Peyton wouldn't have been in that,
that would have been Chloe's spot.

00:41:01.125 --> 00:41:04.862 line:5%,start
She came in here
and had this snotty little attitude,

00:41:04.929 --> 00:41:06.297 line:5%,start
and you back her up.

00:41:06.997 --> 00:41:08.933 line:5%,start
I don't think you guys will have to
put up with me much longer.

00:41:08.999 --> 00:41:10.334 line:5%,start
I'll be gone, this will be it.

00:41:10.401 --> 00:41:11.902 line:5%,start
(sobbing)

00:41:11.969 --> 00:41:13.971 line:5%,start
(tense music playing)

